  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="KT273-kilavi">pirivar eṉak kavaṉṟa talaimakaḷait tōḻi vaṟpuṟuttiyatu. </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">The confidante encouraging HER who was anxious he would
          separate. </p>
      </div>

      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="KT273">
          <l> alkuṟu poḻutiṟ ṟātumukai tayaṅkap</l>
          <l> peruṅkā ṭuḷḷu macaivaḷi pōlat</l>
          <l> taṇṇiya kamaḻu moṇṇuta lōyē</l>
          <l> nontaṉai yāyiṟ kaṇṭatu moḻival</l>
          <l> peruntēṉ kaṇpaṭu varaiyiṉ mutumāl</l>
          <l> paṟiyā tēṟiya maṭavōṉ pōla</l>
          <l> vēmān taṉṟiv vulaka</l>
          <l> nāmuḷē mākap piriyalen teḷimē.</l>
        </lg>

        <lg xml:lang="en">
          <l>O you with bright forehead smelling coolly <note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">
            taṇṇiya </term> has to be taken as an adverb, since nutal "forehead" cannot be construed
            with a n.pl. Or is this meant as an elliptical metaphor for her hair?</note>
          </l>
          <l rend="indent2">like the moving wind which remembers the great wilderness,</l>
          <l rend="indent5">so that buds shimmer with pollen at night time!</l>
          <l>If you were to ache, I speak of what [I have] seen:</l>
          <l>confused is this world,</l>
          <l rend="indent2">like an ignorant person who mounted without knowing</l>
          <l rend="indent5">an old bamboo ladder on the mountain, where a great honey[comb] is
            visible to the eye.</l>
          <l>Let it be clear: we won't separate as we are here.</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
